
You are given an integer `n` representing the number of houses on a number line, numbered from `0` to `n - 1`. Additionally, you are given a 2D integer array `offers` where <code>offers[i] = [start<sub>i</sub>, end<sub>i</sub>, gold<sub>i</sub>]</code>, indicating that <code>i<sup>th</sup></code> buyer wants to buy all the houses from <code>start<sub>i</sub></code> to <code>end<sub>i</sub></code> for <code>gold<sub>i</sub></code> amount of gold.
